  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Final Scientific Dataset Construction**\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook finalizes and validates the dataset used for model training and evaluation. It builds upon the dataset construction pipeline implemented in 00_build_scientific_dataset.ipynb.\n",
        "\n",
        "The earlier notebook performs the initial dataset assembly, including metadata loading, speaker normalization, speaker level dataset splitting, scanning audio files, and generating dataset manifest files using full recordings.\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook reproduces that pipeline while introducing methodological refinements, clip level segmentation, and additional validation procedures to ensure the dataset is suitable for training machine learning models.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Key methodological changes and additions include:**\n",
        "\n",
        "* segmentation of recordings into fixed 30 second clips\n",
        "\n",
        "*   generation of multiple clips per recording rather than treating each recording as a single sample\n",
        "*   use of overlapping clips for training and non overlapping clips for validation and testing to improve training data while preserving clean evaluation\n",
        "*  computation of clip metadata including clip start time, clip duration, and clip index within the original recording\n",
        "*  validation that speakers do not appear in multiple dataset splits through a post construction verification step that programmatically confirms there is no speaker overlap between the train, validation, and test manifests after clip segmentation\n",
        "*  verification of class balance across dataset splits\n",
        "*  duplicate detection adapted for segmented data using (path, clip index) pairs\n",
        "*  analysis of recording duration distributions and clip distributions across splits\n",
        "\n",
        "These extensions build on the original dataset pipeline while maintaining the scientifically sound dataset construction approach established in the earlier notebook.\n",
        "\n",
        "The dataset manifests generated in this notebook are the authoritative dataset files used by the model training pipeline."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6JmcOm_pLX9O"
      }
    },
