      "source": [
        "# Dataset Construction Validation Summary\n",
        "\n",
        "The dataset construction pipeline includes several validation steps to ensure that the resulting dataset is scientifically sound and suitable for training speech classification models.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Speaker Separation\n",
        "\n",
        "All dataset splits were constructed at the **speaker level**, ensuring that recordings from the same individual do not appear in multiple splits. This prevents the model from learning speaker identity rather than dementia related speech patterns.\n",
        "\n",
        "Verification checks confirmed that there is **no overlap of speakers between the training, validation, and test sets**.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Clip Segmentation\n",
        "\n",
        "Clips are generated differently per split:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Training**: 30-second clips with a **20-second stride** (33% overlap). Each new training clip introduces at least 20 seconds of previously unseen speech. A 90s recording yields 4 clips (0, 20, 40, 60); a 55s recording yields 2 clips (0, 20).\n",
        "- **Validation / Test**: 30-second clips with a **30-second stride** (non-overlapping). Non-overlapping segments ensure evaluation metrics are not inflated by correlated clips.\n",
        "\n",
        "The 30-second clip length provides sufficient context to capture cognitive and linguistic markers of dementia such as topic drift, circumlocution, and reduced vocabulary density.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Label Integrity\n",
        "\n",
        "Speaker level label consistency was verified to ensure that each speaker appears with **only one class label** across the dataset.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Duplicate Detection\n",
        "\n",
        "All dataset splits were scanned for duplicate `(path, clip_idx)` pairs. No duplicate clip entries were detected.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Final Dataset Composition\n",
        "\n",
        "After filtering, expansion, and validation, the dataset contains approximately:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **~300–400 training clips** (30s clips, 20s stride)\n",
        "- **~80 validation clips** (30s clips, non-overlapping)\n",
        "- **~38 test clips** (30s clips, non-overlapping)\n",
        "- **~136 unique speakers**"
